pageTitle: Portrait of Dianne Feinstein at the 113th Congress
description: California senator Dianne Feinstein passed away at the age of 90.  After months of declining health she died Thursday night at her home in Washington under a harvest moon.  She began her political career when she was elected to the San Francisco Board of Supervisors in 1969.  A true trailblazer, she was the longest-serving female US senator in history and was known for showing enormous poise.
